---

What IS open-sourced in this repository:
  - Problem-discovery (scanning of known vulnerabilities and malicious components)
  - Offensive-side tooling (red-team attack catalog and runner)
  - Integration clients (plugin, skill, SDK) that talk to OpenGuardrails services

What is NOT open-sourced and remains proprietary:
  - Defensive detection rules, policy engines, and runtime protection logic
  - Threat intelligence ingestion pipelines
  - Backend services operated by OpenGuardrails.com

See docs/PHILOSOPHY.md for the reasoning.
